Educated Professionals: Individuals with higher education, primarily in managerial and intellectual positions.
Intermediate Workers: Individuals with upper secondary education or equivalent, often in intermediate positions.
Employees: Individuals with lower education levels working in employee roles.
High Achievers: Individuals showing high performance, often in managerial roles, with related or significant education.
Low Achievers: Individuals primarily in low-skilled jobs or possess lesser qualifications.
Underqualified Professionals: Individuals who hold managerial positions or intellectual professions but possess lower secondary education, leading to a mismatch in expected qualifications versus actual education level.
Underqualified Workers: Individuals with lower educational qualifications and limited advancement in professional roles.
